TITLE: Subclassing the Call Class in PJSIP C++
DESCRIPTION: Creates a custom call class by subclassing pj::Call to handle call state changes and media state changes. This pattern is required to properly use the Call class in PJSIP.
SOURCE: https://github.com/pjsip/pjproject_docs/blob/master/docs/source/pjsua2/using/call.rst#2025-04-23_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: c++
CODE:
```
class MyCall : public Call
{
public:
    MyCall(Account &acc, int call_id = PJSUA_INVALID_ID)
    : Call(acc, call_id)
    { }

    ~MyCall()
    { }

    // Notification when call's state has changed.
    virtual void onCallState(OnCallStateParam &prm);

    // Notification when call's media state has changed.
    virtual void onCallMediaState(OnCallMediaStateParam &prm);
};
```

