TITLE: Handling Call Disconnection in PJSIP C++
DESCRIPTION: Implements the onCallState callback to properly handle call disconnection. When the call state changes to DISCONNECTED, the call object is deleted to prevent memory leaks and invalid operations.
SOURCE: https://github.com/pjsip/pjproject_docs/blob/master/docs/source/pjsua2/using/call.rst#2025-04-23_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: c++
CODE:
```
void MyCall::onCallState(OnCallStateParam &prm)
{
    CallInfo ci = getInfo();
